  "observations": [
    "The reference shell is represented as a rectangular 10 by 5 metre café.",
    "Table B3 and its route-side chair visibly constrict the declared continuous-route corridor.",
    "The service counter includes a lowered segment and the accessible table includes an empty wheelchair position."
  ],
  "userIntent": [
    "Provide a warm compact café with 14 to 18 capacity positions.",
    "Maintain a continuous step-free journey from entrance to ordering, pick-up, accessible seating and accessible WC.",
    "Make accessibility evidence legible without treating the presentation model as validation truth."
  ],
  "assumptions": [
    "Dimensions describe a concept demo and require site verification before construction.",
    "Structure, fire strategy, plumbing, drainage, ventilation, lighting calculations and local approvals are outside this geometry brief.",
    "The lowered service-counter segment is the modeled approach point for both ordering and pick-up in this compact concept.",
    "The WC fixture is treated as wall-hung and non-floor-obstructing in the two-dimensional turning-zone check; its installation geometry remains unverified.",
    "Declared table-to-chair overlap exemptions represent chairs tucked beneath their associated table footprints.",
    "The validator report, not this presentation brief or its ArchViz GLB, is the only source of pass or fail evidence."
  ],
